  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (environmental gap variant)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). NOTE: validation activities were conducted exclusively under controlled laboratory conditions (22 °C, 1 atm, no EMI characterisation); the deployed operating environment in the OR involves temperature excursions (18–28 °C), variable ambient pressure (hypobaric transport scenarios), and electromagnetic interference from surgical equipment. Only a single temperature point was evaluated; humidity and EMI sensitivity studies are absent.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cpb-hemolysis-mrl2",
