      "rationale": "Validation uses the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry with porcine blood analogue at clinically representative flow rates (3–6 L/min) and speeds (2000–3500 RPM). Geometry and flow regime relevance is high. Environmental relevance is partial: laboratory conditions (22 °C, 1 atm, no EMI) do not span the full OR operating envelope described in the COU. Temperature-dependent blood viscosity effects on shear-induced haemolysis at 18 °C and 28 °C are uncharacterised."
