    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed MRL 2 required levels. Six factors are appropriately scoped out at MRL 2. NIH predictions agree with bench measurements within 12 % and RH < 1 across all five operating points. The assessment team concluded that the model is fit for the stated COU. Temperature sensitivity at 22 °C was confirmed adequate for the nominal laboratory benchmark; the broader OR environmental envelope (18–28 °C temperature range, variable ambient pressure, electromagnetic interference from surgical equipment) was noted in the test-conditions factor narrative but was not the subject of a dedicated sensitivity study or formal bounding analysis. The team judged this gap acceptable given MRL 2 requirements and the availability of physical testing as a complementary evidence source.",
